{
  "answer": "In the final couplet of the ghazal, Ghalib acknowledges knowing the reality of paradise (*jannat ki haqeeqat*), but declares that, for the sake of keeping the heart content, the comforting *khayaal* (notion or fancy) of it remains \"a fine thing\" (*achha hai*), in keeping with the poem's refrain.[^1]\n\nThe full couplet in English translation reads:  \n\"We know the truth of heaven, anyway;  \nBut Ghalib, for the heart's sake, let us say this thought is a fine thing.\"[^1]\n\nIn Romanized transliteration:  \n*Hum ko maaloom hai jannat ki haqeeqat lekin*  \n*Dil ke khush rakhne ko Ghalib yeh khayaal achha hai*.[^2]\n\nIn the original Urdu:  \nہم کو معلوم ہے جنت کی حقیقت لیکن  \nدل کے خوش رکھنے کو غالبؔ یہ خیال اچھا ہے.[^3]\n\n[^1]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/80-husn-e-mah-garche-ba-hangaam-e-kamaal-achha-hai/translation/#p-7c74eb).\n[^2]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/80-husn-e-mah-garche-ba-hangaam-e-kamaal-achha-hai/transliteration/#p-130348).\n[^3]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/80-husn-e-mah-garche-ba-hangaam-e-kamaal-achha-hai/original/#p-24c9c4).",
